(thirdQuint)Buprenorphine for Treatment of Neonatal Abstinence Syndrome in Infants With In Utero Exposure to Benzodiazepines.

 Infants with in utero exposure to opioids often require therapy with morphine for an extended period.

 In a clinical trial, sublingual buprenorphine reduced this treatment period by ~30%.

 However, infants with both opioid and benzodiazepine exposure were not included in the trial.

 This study will test the safety and tolerability of sublingual buprenorphine in infants with in utero exposure to benzodiazepines or who are breastfeeding.

